47 /* Peripheral: AAR */
48 /* Description: Accelerated Address Resolver */
49 
50 /* Register: AAR_TASKS_START */
51 /* Description: Start resolving addresses based on IRKs specified in the IRK data structure */
52 
53 /* Bit 0 : */
54 #define AAR_TASKS_START_TASKS_START_Pos (0UL)
55 #define AAR_TASKS_START_TASKS_START_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_TASKS_START_TASKS_START_Pos)
57 /* Register: AAR_TASKS_STOP */
58 /* Description: Stop resolving addresses */
59 
60 /* Bit 0 : */
61 #define AAR_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Pos (0UL)
62 #define AAR_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_TASKS_STOP_TASKS_STOP_Pos)
64 /* Register: AAR_EVENTS_END */
65 /* Description: Address resolution procedure complete */
66 
67 /* Bit 0 : */
68 #define AAR_EVENTS_END_EVENTS_END_Pos (0UL)
69 #define AAR_EVENTS_END_EVENTS_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_EVENTS_END_EVENTS_END_Pos)
71 /* Register: AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED */
72 /* Description: Address resolved */
73 
74 /* Bit 0 : */
75 #define AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED_EVENTS_RESOLVED_Pos (0UL)
76 #define AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED_EVENTS_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_EVENTS_RESOLVED_EVENTS_RESOLVED_Pos)
78 /* Register: AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED */
79 /* Description: Address not resolved */
80 
81 /* Bit 0 : */
82 #define AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (0UL)
83 #define AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_EVENTS_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
85 /* Register: AAR_INTENSET */
86 /* Description: Enable interrupt */
87 
88 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for NOTRESOLVED event */
89 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
90 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
91 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
92 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
93 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Set (1UL)
95 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for RESOLVED event */
96 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
97 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos)
98 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
99 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
100 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Set (1UL)
102 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for END event */
103 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos (0UL)
104 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos)
105 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Disabled (0UL)
106 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Enabled (1UL)
107 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Set (1UL)
109 /* Register: AAR_INTENCLR */
110 /* Description: Disable interrupt */
111 
112 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for NOTRESOLVED event */
113 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
114 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
115 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
116 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
117 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
119 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for RESOLVED event */
120 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
121 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos)
122 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
123 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
124 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
126 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for END event */
127 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos (0UL)
128 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos)
129 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Disabled (0UL)
130 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Enabled (1UL)
131 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Clear (1UL)
133 /* Register: AAR_STATUS */
134 /* Description: Resolution status */
135 
136 /* Bits 3..0 : The IRK that was used last time an address was resolved */
137 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos (0UL)
138 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Msk (0xFUL << AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos)
140 /* Register: AAR_ENABLE */
141 /* Description: Enable AAR */
142 
143 /* Bits 1..0 : Enable or disable AAR */
144 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
145 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
146 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0UL)
147 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (3UL)
149 /* Register: AAR_NIRK */
150 /* Description: Number of IRKs */
151 
152 /* Bits 4..0 : Number of Identity root keys available in the IRK data structure */
153 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos (0UL)
154 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Msk (0x1FUL << AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos)
156 /* Register: AAR_IRKPTR */
157 /* Description: Pointer to IRK data structure */
158 
159 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the IRK data structure */
160 #define AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Pos (0UL)
161 #define AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Pos)
163 /* Register: AAR_ADDRPTR */
164 /* Description: Pointer to the resolvable address */
165 
166 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the resolvable address (6-bytes) */
167 #define AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Pos (0UL)
168 #define AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Pos)
170 /* Register: AAR_SCRATCHPTR */
171 /* Description: Pointer to data area used for temporary storage */
172 
173 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to a scratch data area used for temporary storage during resolution.A space of minimum 3 bytes must be reserved. */
174 #define AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos (0UL)
175 #define AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos)
